.\" Man page for glassy -- a minimal GPU-accelerated terminal emulator.
.\" Render locally with:  man ./extra/glassy.1
.TH GLASSY 1 "2026-06-19" "glassy 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
glassy \- a minimal, GPU-accelerated terminal emulator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B glassy
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RB [ \-e
.IR COMMAND " [" ARGS ...]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B glassy
is a small, fast, GPU-accelerated terminal emulator written in Rust. It draws
the grid with an instanced
.B wgpu
renderer fed by a dynamic glyph atlas, supports 24-bit truecolor, color emoji
and CJK fallback, procedural box-drawing, text decorations, mouse reporting,
selection, clipboard, scrollback, OSC 8 hyperlinks, and tabs.
.PP
Rendering is on-demand and damage-based: with nothing changing on screen glassy
issues no frames and consumes no CPU, and when the screen does change only the
cells that actually changed are re-rasterized.
.PP
Configuration is read from a simple
.I KEY=VALUE
file (see
.B CONFIGURATION
below); command-line options override the file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-font\-size " PT"
Font size in points. Must be a positive number.
.TP
.BI \-\-font\-family " NAME"
Font family name, or a path to a font file.
.TP
.BI \-\-theme " NAME"
Color theme. One of
.B tokyo\-night
(default) or
.BR catppuccin\-mocha .
An unknown name falls back to Tokyo Night with a warning.
.TP
.BI \-\-opacity " F"
Window opacity as a float from
.B 0.0
(fully transparent) to
.B 1.0
(fully opaque). Values are clamped to that range.
.TP
.BI \-\-padding " PX"
Grid inset padding in logical pixels. Must be \[>=] 0.
.TP
.BI \-\-scrollback " N"
Number of lines of scrollback history to retain.
.TP
.BI \-\-bell\-visual " BOOL"
Flash the window on the terminal bell. Default
.BR true .
Accepts
.BR true / false ", " yes / no ", " on / off ", " 1 / 0 .
.TP
.BI \-\-bell\-audible " BOOL"
Emit a soft beep on the terminal bell. Default
.BR false .
Requires a build with the
.B bell\-audio
feature. Accepts the same boolean spellings as
.BR \-\-bell\-visual .
.TP
.BI \-e ", " \-\-command " COMMAND " [ ARGS ...]
Run
.I COMMAND
(with the remaining arguments) instead of the login shell. This consumes the
rest of the command line verbatim, so it must come last.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B glassy
reads
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/glassy/glassy.conf
(falling back to
.IR ~/.config/glassy/glassy.conf ).
The file is a list of
.I KEY=VALUE
lines. Blank lines and lines beginning with
.B #
or
.B ;
are ignored. Surrounding whitespace and a single layer of matching single or
double quotes are stripped from values. Command-line options override the file.
.PP
Recognized keys:
.TP
.B font_family
Font family name, or a path to a font file.
.TP
.B font_size
Font size in points (positive number). Default
.BR 14 .
.TP
.B theme
Color theme:
.B tokyo\-night
or
.BR catppuccin\-mocha .
Default
.BR tokyo\-night .
.TP
.B opacity
Window opacity from
.B 0.0
to
.BR 1.0 .
Default
.BR 0.92 .
.TP
.B padding
Grid inset in logical pixels (\[>=] 0).
.TP
.B shell
Program plus arguments to run instead of the login shell, e.g.
.IR "/usr/bin/zsh -l" .
.TP
.B scrollback
Lines of scrollback history. Default
.BR 10000 .
.TP
.B bell_visual
Flash the window on the bell. Default
.BR true .
.TP
.B bell_audible
Soft beep on the bell. Default
.BR false " (needs the " bell\-audio " build)."
.PP
Example
.IR glassy.conf :
.PP
.RS
.EX
font_family  = FiraCode Nerd Font Mono
font_size    = 14
theme        = tokyo\-night
opacity      = 0.92
padding      = 6
scrollback   = 10000
bell_visual  = true
bell_audible = false
shell        = /usr/bin/zsh \-l
.EE
.RE
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+C
Copy the current selection to the clipboard.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+V
Paste from the clipboard.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+T
Open a new tab.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+W
Close the current tab.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Tab
Switch to the next tab.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+Tab
Switch to the previous tab.
.TP
.B Ctrl++
Increase the font size.
.TP
.B Ctrl+\-
Decrease the font size.
.TP
.B Ctrl+0
Reset the font size to its configured value.
.TP
.B Shift+PageUp ", " Shift+PageDown
Scroll up / down through the scrollback.
.TP
.B Shift+Home ", " Shift+End
Scroll to the top / bottom of the scrollback.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Left\-click
Open the OSC 8 hyperlink under the pointer.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/glassy/glassy.conf
Primary configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/glassy/glassy.conf
Configuration file used when
.B $XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is unset.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/glassy/fonts/NotoColorEmoji.ttf
Bundled color-emoji font loaded at runtime, if present.
